## A cockpit to monitor / control the status of a home media server running on RaspberryPi

### *** Disclaimer: Written mostly with Claude

* To enable the systemctl (start / stop services) add this line to sudoers via `sudo visudo`:
`$USER ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: /bin/systemctl start *, /bin/systemctl stop *`

* To enable rebooting, add this line to sudoers via `sudo visudo`: `$USER ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: /sbin/reboot`

## How to install service (rpi)
### /etc/systemd/system/pi-dashboard.service
```
[Unit]
Description=Raspberry Pi Dashboard
After=network.target

[Service]
Type=simple
User=nkrueger
WorkingDirectory=/home/nkrueger/dev/rpi_server_cockpit
Environment="PATH=/home/nkrueger/dev/rpi_server_cockpit/.venv/bin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin"
ExecStart=/home/nkrueger/dev/rpi_server_cockpit/.venv/bin/gunicorn --bind 0.0.0.0:5000 --workers 2 --timeout 300 rpi_dashboard:app
Restart=always
RestartSec=10

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target`
```

### Commands to run
```
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl stop pi-dashboard.service
sudo systemctl start pi-dashboard.service
sudo systemctl restart pi-dashboard.service
sudo systemctl status pi-dashboard.service
```